.P
.SH OPTIONS
.P
\fB-n\fR, \fB--row-numbers\fR
.RS 4
Show row numbers.\&
.P
.RE
\fB-r\fR, \fB--reverse\fR
.RS 4
Reverse row order.\& Helpful when sorting.\&
.P
.RE
\fB-t\fR, \fB--title\fR <string>
.RS 4
Add a title above the table.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--border\fR <border>
.RS 4
Select the table border style.\& The default is \fBrounded\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--color\fR <color>
.RS 4
Control color output.\& Valid values: \fBon\fR, \fBoff\fR, \fBauto\fR.\& The default is
\fBon\fR.\& Also honors \fBNO_COLOR\fR and \fBFORCE_COLOR\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--delimiter\fR <char>
.RS 4
Set the delimiter when reading input.\& Defaults to '\&\fB,\fR'\& naturally.\& It
accepts any char, or \fBtab\fR for tab-delimited input.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--digits\fR <int>
.RS 4
Set the number of digits after the decimal for float columns.\& Valid values:
\fB1\fR through \fB6\fR.\& The default is \fB3\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--head\fR <int>
.RS 4
Show the first \fIN\fR data rows.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--select\fR <headers>
.RS 4
Show one or more comma-separated headers.\& This can select a subset of
columns, reorder them, or repeat the same column more than once.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--sort\fR <headers>
.RS 4
Sort rows by one or more comma-separated headers before applying \fB--head\fR
or \fB--tail\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--tail\fR <int>
.RS 4
Show the last \fIN\fR data rows.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--theme\fR <theme>
.RS 4
Select the color theme.\& Valid values: \fBauto\fR, \fBdark\fR, \fBlight\fR.\& The default
is \fBauto\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--vanilla\fR
.RS 4
Disable type inference and numeric formatting.\&
.P
.RE
\fB--width\fR <int>
.RS 4
Set the maximum table width in characters.\& By default, \fBtennis\fR uses the
current terminal width or \fB80\fR if it can'\&t be detected.\&
.P
.RE
.SH BORDERS
.P
Border names are adapted from Nushell table themes, which in turn build on the
\fBtabled\fR crate:
.P
\fBascii_rounded\fR, \fBbasic\fR, \fBbasic_compact\fR, \fBcompact\fR, \fBcompact_double\fR,
\fBdots\fR, \fBdouble\fR, \fBheavy\fR, \fBlight\fR, \fBmarkdown\fR, \fBnone\fR, \fBpsql\fR,
\fBreinforced\fR, \fBrestructured\fR, \fBrounded\fR, \fBsingle\fR, \fBthin\fR, \fBwith_love\fR
.P
.SH EXAMPLES
.P
Render with row numbers and a title:
.P
.RS 4
$ tennis --row-numbers --title Diamonds diamonds.\&csv
.P
.RE
Read from standard input:
.P
.RS 4
$ cat diamonds.\&csv | tennis
.P
.RE
Disable colors and numeric formatting:
.P
.RS 4
$ tennis --color off --vanilla diamonds.\&csv
.P
.RE
Render with a different border:
.P
.RS 4
$ tennis --border dots diamonds.\&csv
.P
.RE
Render a tab-delimited file:
.P
.RS 4
$ tennis --delimiter tab data.\&tsv
.P
.RE
Render a JSON file:
.P
.RS 4
$ tennis data.\&json
.P
.RE
